result.text:
How to make vector illustrations with Midjourney (v6 remastered)

You can make flat vectors in a ton of different styles with MJ.

Here's a prompt and some of my best tips:

Prompt: Simple flat vector illustration of [a young woman sitting at her desk with a laptop], isolated on a white background.

The most important thing is to play with the stylize parameter.

The default value is 100.

Like v5, a lower stylize value makes your image cleaner and more minimalistic.

MJ also follows your instructions more.

For example:

Simple flat vector illustration of a young woman sitting at her desk with a laptop, isolated on a white background. --stylize 0

A higher stylize value makes your image more detailed and artistic.

For example:

Simple flat vector illustration of a young woman sitting at her desk with a laptop, isolated on a white background. --stylize 1000

However, it also makes the images more messy, and MJ won't always listen to your instructions.

.

Now, what's the difference between Midjourney v5 and v6?

By default, v6 is MUCH more detailed and artistic than v5.

It also struggles with minimalistic images.

If you want to fix this, you can:

1. Use a low stylize value between 0 and 100

2. Add "minimalistic" and "plain white background" to the prompt (very important)

3. Add "--style raw" at the end of your prompt

Finally, convert them into .svg files with vectorizer. ai 

That's all for now. Hope it helps!

Follow me at @chaseleantj for more Midjourney guides :)
